	<p>Without the incentive of improving your lot in life, people like Andrew Carnegie, Henry Ford, and J.P. Morgan, just to name a few, would not have done what they did. Had that been the case, we'd still be practically living in the Dark Ages compared to where we are now. The "upper-middle" American lifestyle would be worse than most lower class lifestyles are today. You remove the incentive for significant improvement in lifestyle and you remove all improvement in lifestyle.</p>
	
	
	
