I can only really speak about Ford, as I know some of his companies history, but Ford was NOT a nice guy.  He was a racist bastard who happily worked the holy living snot out of his employees.<br />
<br />
Yes, his industrialization of the auto industry allowed many more people to be able to afford cars.  And yes, it changed the way that we do business and affected one of the core American values.  But for the better?  Tough to say.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
