	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Tevyn</b><br /><i>Define "upper middle class" because I'm absolutely certain your idea of what it is is quite different than mine.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>4) Lifestyle. It's all about lifestyle. The ability to go where you want, do what you want, live where you want. You might need to plan for it in advance, but you can do it, you can choose. <blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Wealth by definition is all about accumulation. That's what wealth is. Lifestyle comes at the expense of wealth.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Fair enough. I'm saying that all of the world could be living a rather opulent lifestyle, but there's no need for the current situation...where 5% of the population holds more wealth than the other 95% combined. Wealth may not be static or finite, but contrary to some claims, it's not without a ceiling either.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Typical response by anybody who is disgruntled about their lot in life. "This sucks and should change. So I'm going to advocate and push for change even though I don't know what to change it to, so let's tear down our existing system without a plan in place for what to replace it with."<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Actually, I have it pretty darn good. I didn't start complaining about the system until I got where I want to be. I have it good, but I'm not<br />
 <blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />I do not discount the possibility of a better system being developed, but after 6000 years, the possibility is extremely remote, especially given your admission that it's been proven to work. <hr size="1" /></blockquote>The possibility is not remote that a better system could be developed, but rather remote that anyone would try to implement it. The problem is, the people in a position to do so, have the least to gain. They are already exploiting the general populace for their own gain. Capitalism works because people get to excersize their own desires to exploit each other, to gain while pushing others down. The problem is, we've created a system whereby people get ahead by thinking this way, so our nature will never evolve until we create a system where you can only get ahead by helping others and working for others.</p>
	
	
	
