	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />It has been proven time and time and time again that if you remove someone's incentive to accomplish something, then he or she will not attempt to accomplish it. If everybody were given an upper-middle class lifestyle, not enough of them would work 3 or 4 days a week to sustain the economy. That's precisely why socialism <i>does not work.</i> <hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />
Very true.  People would go to work I think, but they wouldn't work hard.  The only workable form of government that I can fathom is a blend of capitalism and socialism.  Think about it - we are not a 100% capatilistic society now - that doesn't work either.  What happens is attrocities - massive pollution, over-farming, extinction of certain animals, etc.  What we have is a regulated capitalism.  Capitalism with social qualities - social security, welfare, dissability, environmental regulations, etc.  Basically, our government tells us to be a free capitalistic society, but within these parameters.  <br />
 <br />
Fact is, change only occurs when there is motive.  We can and will be an organized society like some of you are discussing.  Only problem is - there's no incentive to do it until it's late in the game.  Won't be our lifetimes, so GET BACK TO WORK!</p>
	
	
	
